ring the discussion to two heuristic concepts—the "politics of authentication" and "aesthetics of persuasion"—the chapters herein explore how this tension is central to the dynamics of heritage formation worldwide.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aEthnicity. 0aGroup identity. 0aMaterial culture. 0aOriginality (Aesthetics) 0aOriginality (Aesthetics). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aCultural Heritage, Heritage Studies, Materiality, Heritage Formation, Cultural Memory, Collective Memory, Aesthetics.1 aBalkenhol, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerliner, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlanes, Ruy Llera, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChidester, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFernandes Adinolfi, Maria Paula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJethro, Duane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, Birgit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, Birgit, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPort, Mattijs van de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPort, Mattijs van de, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRassool, Ciraj, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReinhardt, Bruno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStengs, Irene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWerneck de Andrade Bakker, André, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWitte, Marleen de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1